hitlock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Max Whitlock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\"}, {\"begin\": 756, \"end\": 759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"score\": 0.9995233915708943, \"rank\": 0.00040178693798770027, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\"}, {\"begin\": 760, \"end\": 766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fraser_River\", \"score\": 0.9998832589493899, \"rank\": 8.764920628352371e-05, \"text\": \"Fraser\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fraser_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fraser_River\"}, {\"begin\": 768, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Skywalker\", \"score\": 0.6132233391401262, \"rank\": 0.6172840790120117, \"text\": \"Luke\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Skywalker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Skywalker\"}, {\"begin\": 773, \"end\": 783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\", \"score\": 0.9998299683631184, \"rank\": 0.00017006055237984505, \"text\": \"Whitehouse\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\"}, {\"begin\": 785, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\", \"score\": 0.7223265068505487, \"rank\": 0.3643869496066869, \"text\": \"Jake\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\"}, {\"begin\": 807, \"end\": 815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Hepworth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0014899966085575e-16, \"text\": \"Hepworth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Hepworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Hepworth\"}, {\"begin\": 871, \"end\": 874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9229504480330928, \"rank\": 0.051847866597540836, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an agonising fourth\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 907}, {\"ngram\": \"the third Games\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 927}, {\"ngram\": \"a row\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 936}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After Andy Murray's epic and diving silver for Tom Daley, Whitlock was hoping to cap a stellar 24 hours forTeam GB's old guard, the 31-year-old chasing a seventh Olympic medal.\", \"from\": 939, \"to\": 1115, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.3504423666732365e-42, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 986, \"end\": 995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.841709431873025e-39, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}, {\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.383715808998916e-27, \"text\": \"Whitlock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\"}, {\"begin\": 1051, \"end\": 1053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9952421946419995, \"rank\": 0.004780549377165169, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a stellar 24 hours\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1042}, {\"ngram\": \"a seventh Olympic medal\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1114}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a team including three Games debutants starting their first final on pommel horse, the apparatus on which Whitlock is two-time reigning champion, there was particular onus on the elder statesman to set the tone.\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1228, \"end\": 1236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.383715808998916e-27, \"text\": \"Whitlock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1128}, {\"ngram\": \"three Games debutants\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1160}, {\"ngram\": \"their first final\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1187}, {\"ngram\": \"pommel horse\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1203}, {\"ngram\": \"two-time reigning champion\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1266}, {\"ngram\": \"particular onus\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"the elder statesman\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1316}, {\"ngram\": \"the tone\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1332}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He did so in good style, a score of 15.266 higher than he or anyone else had managed in qualifying on Saturday and boding well for his attempt at an individual three-peat later in the week.\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1524, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"good style\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1358}, {\"ngram\": \"a score\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1367}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1402}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1445}, {\"ngram\": \"his attempt\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1477}, {\"ngram\": \"an individual three-peat\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1505}, {\"ngram\": \"the week\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike in qualifying, when four gymnasts had competed on each discipline and the lowest score wiped, here there was no margin for error, just three to go on every apparatus and everything to count.\", \"from\": 1526, \"to\": 1723, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"qualifying\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1546}, {\"ngram\": \"four gymnasts\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"each discipline\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1598}, {\"ngram\": \"the lowest score\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"no margin\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1651}, {\"ngram\": \"error\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"every apparatus\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1698}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 1703, \"to\": 1713}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Early on, Britain's novices dovetailed nicely.\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1771, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1735, \"end\": 1742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9558943566456184, \"rank\": 0.04614067064110481, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hepworth delivered a vital 14.8 on rings, where his teammates are at their weakest.\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1855, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hepworth\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1780}, {\"ngram\": \"rings\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1812}, {\"ngram\": \"his teammates\", \"from\": 1820, \"to\": 1833}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Whitehouse missed his landing on vault and the sideline fist-pumping threatened briefly to go flat, Jarman, the world champion, picked up the slack with a dazzling response, though the team effort was still a point down on what had been their best apparatus on the Games's opening day.\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 2146, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Whitehouse\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"his landing\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1890}, {\"ngram\": \"vault\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1899}, {\"ngram\": \"the sideline fist-pumping\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1929}, {\"ngram\": \"Jarman\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 1967}, {\"ngram\": \"the world champion\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1987}, {\"ngram\": \"the slack\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2008}, {\"ngram\": \"a dazzling response\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2033}, {\"ngram\": \"the team effort\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2057}, {\"ngram\": \"a point\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2075}, {\"ngram\": \"their best apparatus\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2118}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games's opening day\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2145}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At halfway, the Brits sat in the bronze medal position, with China already out in front.\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9963639017896894, \"rank\": 0.0027964213379789655, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Brits\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2169}, {\"ngram\": \"the bronze medal position\", \"from\": 2177, \"to\": 2202}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 2230, \"to\": 2235}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Japan, though, having been paired with the Chinese and forecast to push them all the way, were off the pace, hindered by a horrorshow on pommel horse from Daiki Hashimoto, the all-around individual champion in Tokyo and both World Championships since.\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2237, \"end\": 2242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9815533386835061, \"rank\": 0.012029946825509587, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2280, \"end\": 2287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.8094590074364016, \"rank\": 0.22354954516032613, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2392, \"end\": 2407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daiki Hashimoto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\"}, {\"begin\": 2447, \"end\": 2452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999732908694, \"rank\": 2.661944976674687e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pace\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"a horrorshow\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"pommel horse\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2386}, {\"ngram\": \"the all-around individual champion\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2443}, {\"ngram\": \"both World Championships\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2481}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old would later make amends with a clutch show on the high bar to punish China's fatal mistake.\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2574, \"end\": 2579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9963639017896894, \"rank\": 0.0027964213379789655, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"amends\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2528}, {\"ngram\": \"a clutch show\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2547}, {\"ngram\": \"the high bar\", \"from\": 2551, \"to\": 2563}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Towards the business end we went.\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2631, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the business end\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2622}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ukraine were magnificent on parallel bars, the Americans pumped in front of a US-heavy crowd as they put qualifying's demons on the high bar aside.\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2632, \"end\": 2639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9354370633102137, \"rank\": 0.0689755067747729, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"parallel bars\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2673}, {\"ngram\": \"the Americans\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2688}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 2699, \"to\": 2704}, {\"ngram\": \"a US-heavy crowd\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2724}, {\"ngram\": \"qualifying's demons\", \"from\": 2737, \"to\": 2756}, {\"ngram\": \"the high bar\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2772}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So raucous was the reception for the diminutive Fred Richard's landing that you wondered whether the Bercy Arena will be able to bear the strain when Simone Biles leads the women's team out in their own final here tomorrow night.\", \"from\": 2780, \"to\": 3009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2881, \"end\": 2892, \"title\": \"h